               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Ṗawlos</persName>
                  <persName><roleName type="title">ʾabbā </roleName></persName>
                  <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
                  <faith type="EOTC"/>
                  <occupation type="ecclesiastic">monk, writer</occupation>
                  <birth><date>1510</date></birth>
                  <residence></residence>
               <floruit> He was a sixteenth century Ethiopian monk who composed his  personal as well as political life  from  <date>1531</date> to <date>1578</date>. 
                  He received a monastic habit in <date>1531/32</date> in the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2228DabraA">Dabra ʿAbbāy</placeName>. After he travelling around different places  including 
                  <placeName ref="LOC1310Aksum">ʾAksum</placeName>, <placeName ref="LOC2254DabraD">Dabra Dāmmo</placeName>, he settled in the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC1634Ayda">ʿAydā</placeName>
                  . His account provides important historical details about  the war of <persName ref="PRS1500Ahmad">Aḥmad</persName>, 
                  the capture of <placeName ref="PRS7102Minas">Minās</placeName>, the death of <persName ref="PRS4121Fiqtor">Fiqṭor</persName>, the incursion of <ref corresp="ETH1973Oromo">Oromo</ref>, 
                  the death of <persName ref="PRS4406Gaewa">Gāʿǝwā</persName>  and the campiagn of <persName ref="PRS5043hamalmal">Ḥamalmāl</persName></floruit>
                  
                  <death when="1578"></death>
